Now onto the food... ordered the lobster Mac & cheese (a lil peppery), calamari which was pretty good, french fries were ok as well, the salmon with rice and peas and veggies (that barely any) and the Salmon was on the dry side.  Then we had the escovitch fish w/rice & peas and asked for oxtail gravy on the rice (for both dishes) but instead we just got browning sauce.  Now the drinks we ordered were a virgin pina coloda because they didn’t have any regular drinks like juice or soda, a white wine and he recommended the henny sangria which was the only thing correct.  We received a passion fruit drink and a red wine without asking if we wanted it instead.  But was told that their policy doesn’t allow return of drinks (but that’s not what we ordered  They also charged $5.49 for the use of a credit card instead of cash without informing us of the transaction.  Giving them a 3 was generous because they need to do better.

I visited this establishment last night with two friends and experienced the most unprofessional service ever by the manager and waiter/bartender. I was told by the manager who was drinking alllllll night that I was "f***ing ignorant"! Disgusting. We waited 30 minutes before even being given a menu or even a glass of water. I had to approach the bartender who came over 10 minutes later to serve us.  We ordered the coconut shrimp as an appetizer, it never came out until we got our entrees, 20 minutes later. The shrimp were tasty. However, the lobster mac and cheese, which is usually delicious, was bland and watery.  I ordered a sexy storm, substituting the vodka for Hennessy. My server said sure no problem. She later returns at the end of our service and hands us our bill where I was charged 14 additional dollars as an uncharge on a $10 cocktail. I explained to her that she did not disclose there was an upcharge, especially of that amount, for the substitution. She replied saying "Oh I thought I did, but either way did you think you were going to get the Hennessy for free?". That's when the drunk manager came over and became combative and told me he's not fixing it because I drank the drink and if I were in the city I'd pay whatever upcharge they wanted and I was f***ing ignorant.  I'm a social elite! I pride myself in supporting black businesses, as I'm a hardworking West  Indian American myself. I've been to many reputable establishments all over the tri-state and NEVER have I been spoken to or dealt with in such a disrespectful and condescending matter as I did last night. Especially as a paying customer. Unfortunately, that's the last time I'll support this establishment. I'm absolutely appalled!

We would’ve ordered way more food and drinks if they had taken debit. Another thing mentioned on the menu is there is a 25-35min wait for entrees (don’t go starving like I did) and there’s a 15% gratuity for parties of 3 or more. I don’t think our food took that long though!  I would go back prepared with cash so that I can have a drink and try other dishes.

Went here last night to celebrate my best friends birthday 1) Staff was Super Friendly 2) Bartender made amazing drinks 3) Food was yummy Had Salmon Coquets , Jerk Shrimp and pasta My friend had Salmon and rice Only thing I would change is the short ribs I recommend boiling them more to have them falling off the bones Overall great experience

Maybe it was just my bad luck but I went here last night after hearing all about it. Once I got inside, I waited about 10 minutes for a hostess to seat me even though it wasn't busy AT ALL. Once I got a table, I waited about 30 MINUTES for a waitress to ask what I would like to drink. As I was waiting for just simple drinks, waitresses and management were arguing a few feet from our table, then our waitress (I kid  you not)  QUIT right on the spot! Another 30 minutes waiting for my food. It tasted OK. I finally asked for the check and even that took another 15 minutes! The whole night was filled with arguing, extremely loud music, and excessive waiting. I give this place a 2 and not a 1 only because I'm sure if it were any other day then MAYBE it would've been a better experience.
Love the lollipop chicken with waffles. Fast service and polite and polite people. Would come again

Hello my fellow Brooklynites.  If you are looking for a date night spot look no further, Vivid is your place to be.  With tasty food, well made cocktail drinks and vibrant music, you will have a wonderful time. I visited there for the first time on Friday night and was pleasantly  surprised  by the ambiance of the place and the service.  Sashine our server, made my experience  even better by her bright demeanor.  The food, as in all well prepared Caribbean restaurants was flavor full and on point with texture.  I highly recommend  this Bistro for a visit, you will not be disappointed.

Went there today. Had the salmon croquette and thats it. Took a while to get it when i got it i thought would get a lot but there was two. Wished i would have gotten more than two to go. Sas  spicy but very good. I wasnt a fan of the aioli sauce but with i can't complain. Next time i would try it again.
40 minutes and not even a bite! Almost 30 minutes before a drink!

We came here for Caribbean restaurant week in Brooklyn. It's a cute little restaurant with a bar on the side. I was shocked that it wasn't more crowded for a Saturday night. They played some great music. They had a separate Caribbean restaurant week menu. I ordered the Jerk chicken with rice and peas and their rum punch. My friend had the salmon with rice and peas. My food was pretty good even though the portion was smaller. However,  I really can't complain because my meal was only $6. My drink was surprisingly equally delicious and if I didn't have to go work early the next morning I would've had another one. I will definitely return to chill and eat.

"Celebrated at Vivid's on 10/24/14 after work with co-workers and it was fantastic from the appetizers to the dinner and drinks.  The food was good.  It could of been served hot not warm. Surprisingly, there was a bit of karaoke.  Overall, the service was great!!!  OH!!!!watermelon shots...awesome!!!!!

I stopped by to try this restaurant for caribbean restaurant week . the restaurant had security at the door when you enter and your bag is checked before your enter. Similar to what you experience when you go to a night club. the place is not very big and has a bar that took up half of the restaurant. For a Saturday night. it was not crowded at all. My friend ordered the Jerk chicken with rice and peas as well as a rum punch. I had  the honey glazed salmon with rice and peas. I didnt get to try my friends food but she said that it was really good. My salmon was really good but I thought the rice ad peas was just OK. The service was excellent and our waitress was very helpful.
The steamed vegetable dish is awesome.
